summary: This file is the HTML file for a login page. It includes a form with fields for username and password, as well as a submit button. It also includes a header and an error message holder. The file references a CSS file and a JavaScript file for styling and functionality.

This file contains JavaScript code that handles the login functionality of a web page. It selects the login form, login button, and login error message elements from the HTML document and adds an event listener to the login button. When the login button is clicked, the code prevents the default form submission behavior, retrieves the username and password values from the form, and checks if they match the expected values. If the values match, an alert is displayed and the page is reloaded. If the values do not match, the login error message is displayed.

This file contains CSS styling rules for the login page of a website. It sets the height of the HTML and body elements to 100%, applies a grid layout to the body element, and centers its contents both horizontally and vertically. The main login form is contained within a white box with rounded corners and a drop shadow. The error message that appears if the user enters incorrect login credentials is also styled with a red border and background color. The login form fields have a bottom border and a placeholder text color of #3a3a3a. The submit button has a dark background color, white text, and rounded corners.
